A man has been arrested for allegedly killing his girlfriend, living with albinism in KwaMbonambi KwaZulu-Natal.The 30-year-old man was arrested on Tuesday at Ingwavuma area where he was hiding for the police.Provincial spokesperson Thulani Zwane said, &#8220;On 24 May KwaMbonambi police, opened a missing person docket after a 19-year-old victim, Asanda Mbuyazi went missing. The police together with community members started to search for the victim.Mbuyazi&#8217;s naked body was found in the bushes at Ndlabeyilandula area on 26 May 2017.&#8220;She had stab wounds on her body and without her underwear which made police to suspect that she was raped,&#8221; said Zwane.KZN Acting Provincial Commissioner, Major General Bheki Langa commended the members who worked tirelessly in tracing the murder suspect. We once again condemn the killing of people living with albinism in the province. I must commend our detectives and uniformed members who worked tirelessly immediately once the victim was reported missing. Our detectives will meticulously investigate this case and ensure that the suspect is prosecuted and convicted, said Langa.The suspect will be charged with rape and murder and will appear in the KwaMbonambi Magistrates Court soon.